welcome_message_body: Welcome to Obando, Philippines! Known for its colorful festivals and rich cultural heritage, we invite you to explore our charming city and immerse yourself in the lively atmosphere. Enjoy your stay!

terminals.name: Terminal 1
terminals.description: The oldest and largest terminal at Ninoy Aquino International Airport, serving international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 2
terminals.description: Also known as the Centennial Terminal, it serves as the main hub for Philippine Airlines.

terminals.name: Terminal 3
terminals.description: The newest and largest terminal at Ninoy Aquino International Airport, serving both international and domestic flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 4
terminals.description: Also known as the Domestic Terminal, it serves as the hub for local airlines.

wifi.note: WiFi is available for free for 2 hours. Additional hours can be purchased for a fee.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Baler Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.
